        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="0.01" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Temporary price data. Calculated as 90% of purchasers price based on: Average European district heat price from Ecoheatcool and Euroheat 2005-2006, Ecoheat Work package 1: The European heat market. Final report. http://www.solarthermalworld.org/files/Ecoheatcool%20WP1%20Web.pdf?download</comment>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimation. This value does not reflect real conditions. The annual production volume determines the shares of supplying activities on a certain market. 
The share of heat, central or small-scale, natural gas from CHP plants was assumed to amount to 4%; the share from pure heat plants was assumed to amount to 96%. The annual production volumes of all supplying datasets reflect these shares on the market, but are not realistic production volumes. Identical shares for all 7 boiler types producing heat from natural gas on a small-scale are assumed.

See talk pages for further discussion of the modelling of the heat markets.

//
Previous comment and production volume: 
Consumption in residential and small-scale applications (IEA Balance tables: 25 EJ net calorific value = 27.84 EJ gross calorific value), divided evenly over 7 boiler types, multiplied by the conversion efficiency of the boiler type on a gross calorific value basis (86.4%)
3.4365E+12MJ</productionVolumeComment>
